gomodel:SYNGO_2343  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Shisa6 interacts with Dlg4/PSD95 in (fig 3, hippocampal neurons, FRET) and decreases AMPAR mobility through its PDZ-binding domain (fig 4, hippocampal neurons, Single-nanoparticle tracking of surface AMPARs).. Experimental description: \"Hippocampal neurons derived from 18-day-old rat embryos of either sex were cultured following the Banker protocol\"\n\nSingle particle tracking assay in figure 4, exerpt from M&M;\n\"For endogenous GluA2 QD tracking, rat hippocampal neurons were ...\"\n\n24/01/2018 Pim\n- Over-expressed Shisa6 is of mouse species: \"The full-length coding DNA for exon3-containing mouse Shisa6 was obtained from Genscript as a pENTR4 construct (\"\n- Annotation to mouse was made based on the overexpressed protein in Fig.4" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-01-24" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2343" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

